<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="16" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[227,372,725,751]" box="[227,372,725,751]" pageId="16" pageNumber="83">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,725,751]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="83" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,725,751]" pageId="16" pageNumber="83">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[227,1437,772,1010]" pageId="16" pageNumber="83">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,772,798]" pageId="16" pageNumber="83">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30459.1 is a phragmocone fragment of a quarter whorl without shell preservation (
<figureCitation box="[235,343,807,833]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[227,270,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[271,1388,1255,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-219@16.[271,1392,1249,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 11. Stroboceras ancilis sp. nov. from Timimoun (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype" pageId="16" pageNumber="83">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). It has a depressed pentagonal whorl profile and is widest at about the middle of the flank. The outer half of the flank is occupied by a shallow longitudinal groove, delimited on the ventral side by an angular ventrolateral shoulder and on the umbilical side by a rounded ridge. On the venter, near the ventrolateral shoulder, there is a finer ridge accompanied on both sides by a shallow longitudinal groove. The venter is slightly concave. The umbilical wall is oblique and almost flat; it ends at the umbilical seam. There is a small, very shallow dorsal whorl zone (
<figureCitation box="[887,996,983,1009]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[227,270,649,675]" captionTargetBox="[343,1319,302,591]" captionTargetId="figure-361@17.[343,1319,302,591]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 12. Stroboceras ancilis sp. nov. from Timimoun (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30459.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30459.1, at ww =11.6 mm, wh =8.8 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30459.2. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30459.2, at ww = 10.4 mm, wh =7.1 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="83">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[227,1439,1049,1180]" pageId="16" pageNumber="83">
The suture line shows four rounded lobes each on the venter, flank, umbilical wall and dorsal whorl zone (
<figureCitation box="[235,345,1084,1110]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[227,270,649,675]" captionTargetBox="[343,1319,302,591]" captionTargetId="figure-361@17.[343,1319,302,591]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 12. Stroboceras ancilis sp. nov. from Timimoun (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30459.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30459.1, at ww =11.6 mm, wh =8.8 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30459.2. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30459.2, at ww = 10.4 mm, wh =7.1 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="83">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
). Of these, the rounded V-shaped external lobe is the deepest; the lateral lobe is somewhat asymmetrical and broadly rounded and the lobe on the umbilical wall is shallow. The internal lobe is small and broadly V-shaped.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[227,1437,2001,2027]" pageId="16" pageNumber="83" startId="16.[227,270,2001,2027]" targetBox="[271,1388,1255,1949]" targetPageId="16">
