<caption pageId="17" pageNumber="84" startId="17.[227,270,649,675]" targetBox="[343,1319,302,591]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph blockId="17.[225,1437,649,782]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,320,649,675]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Fig. 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[327,554,649,675]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroboceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ancilis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,554,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Stroboceras ancilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[562,653,650,676]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Timimoun (both Korn 
<emphasis box="[993,1045,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">et al</emphasis>
. 2002 Coll.). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1209,1230,649,675]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">A</emphasis>
. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30459.1. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,553,685,711]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">B</emphasis>
. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30459.1, at ww =11.6 mm, wh =8.8 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,248,720,746]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">C</emphasis>
. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30459.2. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[746,767,720,746]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">D</emphasis>
. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30459.2, at ww = 10.4 mm, wh =7.1 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="17.[226,1436,870,1002]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
The 
<typeStatus box="[279,391,871,897]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">paratypes</typeStatus>
show little variation in conch shape and suture line. The ww/wh ratio is between 1.30 and 
<quantity box="[226,307,906,932]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5559999999999996" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" unit="in" value="1.4">1.40 in</quantity>
all specimens and the whorl profile has a very similar shape. 
<typeStatus box="[1018,1121,906,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30459.2 (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1421,906,932]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[227,270,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[271,1388,1255,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-219@16.[271,1392,1249,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 11. Stroboceras ancilis sp. nov. from Timimoun (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
), however, shows slightly more sharply defined longitudinal ridges; its suture line (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1287,941,967]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[227,270,649,675]" captionTargetBox="[343,1319,302,591]" captionTargetId="figure-361@17.[343,1319,302,591]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 12. Stroboceras ancilis sp. nov. from Timimoun (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30459.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30459.1, at ww =11.6 mm, wh =8.8 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30459.2. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30459.2, at ww = 10.4 mm, wh =7.1 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
) has slightly shallower lobes than the 
<typeStatus box="[518,625,976,1002]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[227,1436,1041,1103]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
<typeStatus box="[227,330,1042,1068]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30459.3 is a heavily corroded specimen 
<quantity box="[928,1016,1042,1068]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 mm</quantity>
in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1301,1041,1068]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[227,270,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[271,1388,1255,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-219@16.[271,1392,1249,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 11. Stroboceras ancilis sp. nov. from Timimoun (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Although incomplete, it shows the general advolute conch form with whorls touching the preceding.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
