<paragraph blockId="17.[227,1436,1189,1250]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,454,1189,1215]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroboceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ancilis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,454,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Stroboceras ancilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[463,554,1189,1215]" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all other species of the genus by its almost rectangular whorl profile with a right-angled ventrolateral shoulder.
</paragraph>
